Energetic singer D’banj has been trending for some time on social media platforms after making his first appearance as a judge on Nigerian Idol. Fans of the Kokomaster do not seem to get enough of him as he was number two on Nigeria’s Twitter trend list. The fans applauded the organisers’ decision to bring the self-acclaimed entertainer on board.   M.I. urges colleagues to get PVCs     Cremate my body when I die – Femi Kuti     Olamide hints at retiring after 12th album   “Whosever made Dbanj part of the judges made a very good decision,” a fan tweeted. - Advertisement - Another fan wrote: “Dbanj on his own, will make the Nigerian Idols trend… His facial Expressions ehn.” “Ahhhh Dbanj you will need more than one night… And I was a bit moody before, see me laughing my ass out whoever made Dbanj the judge made the right choice… He is hilarious funny plus comedian too ooo.” D’banj and Simi replaced DJ Sose and Seyi Shay respectively for the seventh edition of the reality cum talent show.